The paper deals with the problem of selecting small groups of itemsets that represent the data well, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The use of decision trees and MDL for compression is a common technique in the field of machine learning, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of finding complex interactions between attributes, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of decision trees and MDL also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of selecting small subsets of itemsets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
